pageTitle: Plymouth Argyle - Premier League Ref For Argyle Cup Game
TableContextTimeStampBeforeTable: {18301=Date:Friday November 30 2012, 18255=Time: 9:11AM, 12091=Reid Second Favourite To Be Top Scorer (Sunday July 19 2015), 12835=Top South West Club? (Friday July 24 2015), 13428=JPT Celebrates Ten Years - Plymouth Argyle (Tuesday July 28 2015), 13025=Argyle 2 - 1 Reading U21 (Saturday July 25 2015), 12467=Bath Impressions (Tuesday July 21 2015), 11704=Argyle Appoint Jon (Friday July 17 2015), 11890=Bideford Impressions (Saturday July 18 2015), 12652=Argyle Sign Boateng (Thursday July 23 2015), 13221=Where Are They Now - Harry Wilcox (Monday July 27 2015), 12287=Where Are They Now - Chris Billy (Monday July 20 2015), 21202=Premier League referee Roger East will be in charge of Plymouth Argyle's Johnstone's Paint Trophy clash against Oxford United on Tuesday. The Wiltshire-based ref is in his first season in the top flight, officiating in three Premier League games so far. East was also the referee for Argyle's Devon Derby game against Torquay United in September and has been a regular in the Championship this season. East will be assisted at Home Park by Andrew Bennett and Brett Huxtable. The Southern Section Quarter-final on Tuesday 4th December will kick-off at 7pm. The tie will be settled on the night with no extra time. If the scores are level after 90 minutes the outcome will be decided by a penalty shoot-out. Each team must play at least six regular first-teamers, based on overall appearances or previous games. Argyle are ranked at 11/8 to win the game, Oxford placed at 9/5 to win and the draw has odds of 9/4 at 90 minutes.}
